{"questionId":"20278","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A biased four-sided die, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, is rolled. Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> be the score obtained when die <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> is rolled. The&nbsp;probability distribution for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> is given in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a5b8be9c77e3780136f9d84a7182640003ee7120.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognising probabilities sum to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20278","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of p.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}